---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Panel from "../components/ui/Panel.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Code of Conduct">
  <section class="container page" aria-labelledby="coc-title">
    <h1 id="coc-title" class="page-title">Code of Conduct</h1>
    <p class="page-intro">Standards and expectations for all Ghostbusters Virginia members.</p>

    <p class="coc-preamble">
      Ghostbusters, Virginia recognizes that our members portray characters and ideas from the
      Ghostbusters Universe, which is owned by Sony Corporation. As such, members carry the
      responsibility of portraying these characters professionally and with respect while in public
      or when representing themselves as a steward of Ghostbusters, Virginia. For these reasons, all
      members are prohibited from acting in a manner disrespectful toward the image they are
      portraying, toward fellow club members, or toward the public at large while in costume at an
      event or acting as a representative of the group. Examples of unacceptable conduct include,
      but are not limited to, the following:
    </p>

    <Panel heading="Public Image" headingLevel={2}>
      <p>
        Foul language, obscene gestures, and use of alcohol or tobacco are not allowed while in
        costume in view of the public (especially children) as it jeopardizes the group's image. Any
        convention or gathering where adult content is prevalent may be considered a private venue
        and a non-Ghostbusters event and behavioral standards shall be relaxed on an equivalent
        basis in consideration.
      </p>
    </Panel>

    <Panel heading="Prohibited Behavior" headingLevel={2}>
      <p>
        Acting in a threatening or violent manner, sexual harassment or misconduct, theft, breaking
        the law, and illegal substance abuse are all prohibited and considered unacceptable
        behavior. This applies to members in or out of costume at events or while representing the
        Ghostbusters, Virginia.
      </p>
    </Panel>

    <Panel heading="Digital Communication" headingLevel={2}>
      <p>
        Breaking any established Ghostbusters, Virginia forum or social media rules and policies, in
        grossly negligent volume, will cause a member to be banned. This item specifically shall
        pertain to only those means of digital communication as established and administered by the
        Ghostbusters, Virginia.
      </p>
    </Panel>

    <Panel heading="Merchandise" headingLevel={2}>
      <p>
        Creating and distributing unauthorized merchandise which contains "Ghostbusters, Virginia"
        name or logo is forbidden. All merchandise bearing Ghostbusters, Virginia logos must be
        approved by the Merchandising and Branding Officer.
      </p>
    </Panel>

    <Panel heading="Non-Discrimination" headingLevel={2}>
      <p>
        Being discriminatory, verbally or physically abusive, or acting out in bad taste is not
        tolerated. Members will not discriminate based on race, nationality, creed, color, gender,
        disability, or sexual orientation. Members who engage in such conduct may be subject to
        Oversight/Disciplinary committee inquiry and disciplinary action, including expulsion from
        Ghostbusters, Virginia. This code is meant to give fair warning and not restrict freedom. In
        or out of costume, members are required to observe reasonable behavioral standards towards
        fellow members and the general public.
      </p>
    </Panel>

    <Panel heading="Props & Equipment Safety" headingLevel={2}>
      <p>
        Acting irresponsibly with prop equipment/weaponry is considered unacceptable behavior.
        Equipment/Weapons are key components to Ghostbusters costuming; however, Ghostbusters,
        Virginia places the utmost importance upon the safety of our members as well as the safety
        of the general public while attending events. Ghostbusters, Virginia members are required to
        abide by all relevant Federal, State, and local laws pertaining to weapons, as well as the
        individual rules and policies of specific venues and events. When carrying or displaying
        props, members are expected to behave responsibly and use common sense at all times. Members
        should not point weapons at other persons, act aggressively, behave erratically, or exhibit
        any similar behavior which could result in a public safety issue. For more information on
        equipment, please refer to the Equipment Policies in the Operations Protocols.
      </p>
    </Panel>

    <Panel heading="Masks & Facial Coverings" headingLevel={2}>
      <p>
        Mask and facial covering requirements at events shall be adhered to at all times in
        accordance with Federal, State, and local laws pertaining to mask and facial coverings, as
        well as the individual rules and policies of specific venues and events.
      </p>
    </Panel>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page :global(.panel) {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .coc-preamble {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
  }
</style>
